And when they came to Capernaum, those who collected the two drachmas came to Peter and said, “Doesn’t your teacher pay the two drachmas?”
He said: “Yes.” When he entered the house, Jesus preceded him, saying: “What do you think, Simon? From whom do the rulers of the earth take toll or tribute? From their own children or from the foreigners?”
Peter said to him, “I am a foreigner.” Jesus said to him, “If the sons are free, then the father is also free.”
But lest we disturb them, go to the sea and cast your net, and the first fish that comes up, take it; and when you open its mouth you will find a ring, take it and give it to them in my name and in your name.
